{"id": "EUVD-2022-54521", "enisaUuid": "39636fac-1bfb-3214-89d2-3428cb33904c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nirqchip/realtek-rtl: Fix refcount leak in map_interrupts\n\nof_find_node_by_phandle() returns a node pointer with refcount\nincremented, we should use of_node_put() on it when not need anymore.\nThis function doesn't call of_node_put() in error path.\nCall of_node_put() directly after of_property_read_u32() to cover\nboth normal path and error path.", "datePublished": "2025-02-26T02:24:30", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-01T20:17:05", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e85b1b797de0e7a271b906291ce28245822820b8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f6d6223df0666fbc054e3a8c6ac14eb0af37c286", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/eff4780f83d0ae3e5b6c02ff5d999dc4c1c5c8ce"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49714"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "16e80a10-4657-3fa8-929e-0e1ae018a8ee", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9f3a0f34b84ad1b9a8f2bdae44b66f16685b2143 <e85b1b797de0e7a271b906291ce28245822820b8"}, {"id": "1dd91c19-0327-30cd-9deb-1f94cf42ef17", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.18.6"}, {"id": "5a151ad3-15d0-35ae-a653-dfa0e3ec3387", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.49"}, {"id": "5cd70e5f-cd96-3984-adda-dc9c1e60944e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "7d5a2e0c-bd1e-3588-a253-7b534687cf50", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9f3a0f34b84ad1b9a8f2bdae44b66f16685b2143 <eff4780f83d0ae3e5b6c02ff5d999dc4c1c5c8ce"}, {"id": "b98206e6-8ca5-3330-8757-2e8417e8286e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.12"}, {"id": "c2a5a6be-733b-3e6a-8c93-155c82ffe955", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9f3a0f34b84ad1b9a8f2bdae44b66f16685b2143 <f6d6223df0666